The following assumptions were made regarding the financial plan:
&nbsp;
* Predicted sales growth of 12\%

Now, let us compute the increase in the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Increase in Sales}&=\text{Sales}\times\text{Rate of Increase}\\[12pt]
&={\$46,298,115}\times{12\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$5,555,773.80}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The increase in the sales amounts to \$5,555,773.80.**

Now, let us compute the projected sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Sales}&=\text{Sales}+\text{Increase in Sales}\\[12pt]
&={\$46,298,115}+{\$5,555,773.80}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$51,853,888.80}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected sales is \$51,853,888.80.**

Now, let us compute the percentage of cost in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Cost}&=\frac{\text{Cost}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$34,536,913}{\$46,298,115}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.75}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{75\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of cost in proportion to the sales is 75\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected cost:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Cost}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$51,853,888.80}\times{75\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$38,890,416.60}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected cost is \$38,890,416.60.**

Now, let us compute the percentage of Other Expenses in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Other Expenses}&=\frac{\text{Other Expenses}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$5,870,865}{\$46,298,115}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.12}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{12\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of Other Expenses in proportion to the sales is 12\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected Other Expenses:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Other Expenses}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$51,853,888.80}\times{12\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$6,222,466.66}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Other Expenses is \$6,222,466.66.**

Now, let us compute the percentage of Depreciation in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Depreciation}&=\frac{\text{Depreciation}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$2,074,853}{\$46,298,115}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.04}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{4\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of Depreciation in proportion to the sales is 4\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected Depreciation:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Depreciation}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$51,853,888.80}\times{4\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$2,074,155.55}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Depreciation is \$2,074,155.55.**

Now, let us compute the projected taxable income:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Taxable Income}&=\text{Earnings before Interest and Taxes}\\[5pt]
&-\text{Interest Paid}\\[12pt]
&={\$4,666,849.99}-{\$725,098}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$3,941,751.99}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Taxable income is \$3,941,751.99.**

Now, let us compute the taxes:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Taxes}&=\text{Taxable Income}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$3,941,751.99}\times{21\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$827,767.92}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected taxes is \$827,767.92.**

Now, let us compute the projected net income:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Net Income}&=\text{Taxable Income}-\text{Taxes}\\[12pt]
&={\$3,941,751.99}-{\$827,767.92}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$3,113,984.07}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected net income is \$3,113,984.07.**

The following assumptions were made regarding the financial plan:
&nbsp;
* Additional Fixed assets amounting to \$5,000,000.

Now, let us compute the percentage of cash in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Cash}&=\frac{\text{Cash}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$524,963}{\$46,298,115}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.0113}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{1.13\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of cash in proportion to the sales is 1.13\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected Cash:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Cash}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$51,853,888.80}\times{1.13\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$585,948.94}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Cash is \$585,948.94.**

Now, let us compute the percentage of accounts receivable in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Accounts Receivable}&=\frac{\text{Accounts Receivable}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$843,094}{\$46,298,115}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.02}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{2\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of accounts receivable in proportion to the sales is 2\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected Accounts Receivable:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Accounts Receivable}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$51,853,888.80}\times{2\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$1,037,077.78}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Accounts Receivable is \$1,037,077.78.**

Now, let us compute the percentage of Inventory in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage of Inventory}&=\frac{\text{Inventory}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$1,235,161}{\$46,298,115}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.03}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{3\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of Inventory in proportion to the sales is 3\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected Inventory :
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Inventory }&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$51,853,888.80}\times{3\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$1,555,616.66}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Inventory is \$ 1,555,616.66.**

The percentage of sales of total current assets is as follows:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Total Current Assets}&=\text{Cash}+\text{Accounts Receivable}+\text{Inventory}\\[12pt]
&={1.13\%+2\%+3\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{6.13\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of sales of total current assets is 6.13\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected Current Assets:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Current Assets}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$51,853,888.80}\times{6.13\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$3,178,643.38}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Current Assets is \$3,178,643.38.**

To compute the total fixed assets:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Total Fixed Assets}&=\text{Net Plant and Equipment}+\text{Additional}\\[12pt]
&={\$20,381,945}+{\$5,000,000}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$25,381,945}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The total fixed assets is \$25,381,945.**

Now, let us compute the percentage of Net Plant and Equipment in proportion to the sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Percentage}&=\frac{\text{ Net Plant and Equipment}}{\text{Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$25,381,945}{\$46,298,115}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.44}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{55\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of Net Plant and Equipment in proportion to the sales is 55\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected Net Plant and Equipment:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Net Plant and Equipment}&=\text{Projected Sales}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$51,853,888.80}\times{55\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$28,519,641.59 }\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected Net Plant and Equipment is \$28,519,641.59 .**

The percentage of sales of total assets is as follows:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Total Assets}&=\text{Current Assets}+\text{Fixed Assets}\\[12pt]
&={6.13\%+55\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{61.13\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The percentage of sales of total assets is 61.13\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected Total Assets:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Total Assets}&=\text{Current Assets}+\text{Fixed Assets}\\[12pt]
&={\$3,178,643.38+\$28,519,641.59 }\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$31,698,285.16 }\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The total assets is \$31,698,285.16 .**

Now, let us compute the dividend payout ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Dividend Payout Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Dividend}}{\text{Net Income}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$705,000}{\$2,317,789}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.30}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{30\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The dividend payout ratio is 30\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected dividend:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Dividend}&=\text{Net Income}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$3,113,984.07}\times{30\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$934,195.22}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected dividend is \$934,195.22.**

Now, let us compute the retention ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Retention Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Retained Earnings}}{\text{Net Income}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$1,612,789}{\$2,317,789}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.70}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{70\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The retention ratio is 70\%.**

Now, let us compute the projected retained earnings:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Projected Retained Earnings}&=\text{Net Income}\times\text{Rate}\\[12pt]
&={\$3,113,984.07}\times{70\%}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$2,179,788.85}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The projected addition to the retained earnings is \$2,179,788.85.**

The balance sheet and the corresponding percentage of sales of the accounts are as follows:
&nbsp;
!['slader'](https://slader-solution-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/53254e9f-43ab-4836-8bb9-f1754281460b-1640943895459221.png)

Now, let us prepare the partial pro forma balance sheet of the company:
&nbsp;
!['slader'](https://slader-solution-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/1a1eab70-6b87-40f6-816c-981d70655c16-1640944302426599.png)

Now, to determine the capacity utilization of the company, let us determine the capacity intensity ratio:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Capacity Intensity Ratio}&=\frac{\text{Sales}}{\text{Fixed Assets}}\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$46,298,115}{\$20,381,945}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{2.27}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The capacity intensity ratio is 2.27.**

Now, let us compute the full capacity sales:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Full Capacity Sales}&=\text{Capacity Intensity Ratio}\times\text{New Fixed Assets}\\[12pt]
&={2.27}\times{\$25,381,945}\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{\$57,610,015.15}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The full capacity sales is \$57,610,015.15.**

Now, let us compute the capacity utilization of the company:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Capacity Utilization}&=\frac{\text{Actual Sales}}{\text{Full Capacity Sales}}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\frac{\$51,853,888.80}{\$57,610,015.15}\times100\\[12pt]
&={0.90}\times100\\[12pt]
&=\boxed{90\%}\\
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;
**The capacity utilization is 90\%.**
